--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- The `Structural` predicate: "no `Agen` subterm anywhere".

data Structural : ‚ąÄ {A B} ‚Üí HomTerm A B ‚Üí Set where
  structural-id : ‚ąÄ {A} ‚Üí Structural (id {A})
  structural-őĽ‚áí : ‚ąÄ {A} ‚Üí Structural (őĽ‚áí {A})
  structural-őĽ‚áź : ‚ąÄ {A} ‚Üí Structural (őĽ‚áź {A})
  structural-ŌĀ‚áí : ‚ąÄ {A} ‚Üí Structural (ŌĀ‚áí {A})
  structural-ŌĀ‚áź : ‚ąÄ {A} ‚Üí Structural (ŌĀ‚áź {A})
  structural-őĪ‚áí : ‚ąÄ {A B C} ‚Üí Structural (őĪ‚áí {A} {B} {C})
  structural-őĪ‚áź : ‚ąÄ {A B C} ‚Üí Structural (őĪ‚áź {A} {B} {C})
  structural-ŌÉ  : ‚ąÄ {A B} ‚¶É s : Symm ‚Č§ Symm ‚¶Ą
                ‚Üí Structural (ŌÉ {A = A} {B = B} ‚¶É s ‚¶Ą)
  structural-‚ąė  : ‚ąÄ {A B C} {h : HomTerm B C} {k : HomTerm A B}
                ‚Üí Structural h ‚Üí Structural k
                ‚Üí Structural (h ‚ąė k)
  structural-‚äó  : ‚ąÄ {A B C D} {h : HomTerm A B} {k : HomTerm C D}
                ‚Üí Structural h ‚Üí Structural k
                ‚Üí Structural (h ‚äó‚āĀ k)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Atomic structural constructors are structural.  (The `Agen` atomic
-- constructor is excluded ‚ÄĒ it has `nE ‚Č° 1` and is handled separately.)

Atomic-non-Agen‚ÜíStructural
  : ‚ąÄ {A B} {f : HomTerm A B}
  ‚Üí Atomic f ‚Üí nE ‚ü™ f ‚üę ‚Č° 0 ‚Üí Structural f
Atomic-non-Agen‚ÜíStructural (atomic-Agen _)   ()
Atomic-non-Agen‚ÜíStructural atomic-id         _ = structural-id
Atomic-non-Agen‚ÜíStructural atomic-őĽ‚áí         _ = structural-őĽ‚áí
Atomic-non-Agen‚ÜíStructural atomic-őĽ‚áź         _ = structural-őĽ‚áź
Atomic-non-Agen‚ÜíStructural atomic-ŌĀ‚áí         _ = structural-ŌĀ‚áí
Atomic-non-Agen‚ÜíStructural atomic-ŌĀ‚áź         _ = structural-ŌĀ‚áź
Atomic-non-Agen‚ÜíStructural atomic-őĪ‚áí         _ = structural-őĪ‚áí
Atomic-non-Agen‚ÜíStructural atomic-őĪ‚áź         _ = structural-őĪ‚áź
Atomic-non-Agen‚ÜíStructural (atomic-ŌÉ ‚¶É s ‚¶Ą)  _ = structural-ŌÉ ‚¶É s ‚¶Ą

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Main syntactic lemma: a 0-edge HomTerm is structural.
--
-- Proceeds by induction on `g`.  For atomic constructors, route via
-- `Atomic-non-Agen‚ÜíStructural` (and explicitly rule out `Agen`).  For
-- compound constructors, split the additive 0 into both summands.

nE-0‚ÜíStructural
  : ‚ąÄ {A B} (g : HomTerm A B) ‚Üí nE ‚ü™ g ‚üę ‚Č° 0 ‚Üí Structural g
nE-0‚ÜíStructural (Agen _)              ()
nE-0‚ÜíStructural id                    _ = structural-id
nE-0‚ÜíStructural őĽ‚áí                    _ = structural-őĽ‚áí
nE-0‚ÜíStructural őĽ‚áź                    _ = structural-őĽ‚áź
nE-0‚ÜíStructural ŌĀ‚áí                    _ = structural-ŌĀ‚áí
nE-0‚ÜíStructural ŌĀ‚áź                    _ = structural-ŌĀ‚áź
nE-0‚ÜíStructural őĪ‚áí                    _ = structural-őĪ‚áí
nE-0‚ÜíStructural őĪ‚áź                    _ = structural-őĪ‚áź
nE-0‚ÜíStructural (ŌÉ ‚¶É s ‚¶Ą)             _ = structural-ŌÉ ‚¶É s ‚¶Ą
nE-0‚ÜíStructural (h ‚ąė k) g-nE‚Č°0 =
  -- `nE ‚ü™ h ‚ąė k ‚üę = nE ‚ü™ k ‚üę + nE ‚ü™ h ‚üę` definitionally (see `nE-‚ąė`
  -- in AtomicCompound.agda ‚ÄĒ note the order: it's `nE k + nE h`).
  structural-‚ąė
    (nE-0‚ÜíStructural h (m+n‚Č°0‚áín‚Č°0 (nE ‚ü™ k ‚üę) g-nE‚Č°0))
    (nE-0‚ÜíStructural k (m+n‚Č°0‚áím‚Č°0 (nE ‚ü™ k ‚üę) g-nE‚Č°0))
nE-0‚ÜíStructural (h ‚äó‚āĀ k) g-nE‚Č°0 =
  structural-‚äó
    (nE-0‚ÜíStructural h (m+n‚Č°0‚áím‚Č°0 (nE ‚ü™ h ‚üę) g-nE‚Č°0))
    (nE-0‚ÜíStructural k (m+n‚Č°0‚áín‚Č°0 (nE ‚ü™ h ‚üę) g-nE‚Č°0))

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Narrowed postulate: symmetric-monoidal coherence on the structural
-- fragment, at the `FreeMonoidal` level.
--
-- This is the *minimal* postulate needed to discharge the original
-- `decode-rel-resp-‚ČÖŠīī-atomic-compound-0E`.  It is the statement of
-- Mac Lane's symmetric monoidal coherence theorem on the structural
-- (i.e. generator-free) sub-language: any two `Structural` HomTerms
-- of the same type whose hypergraph translations are isomorphic are
-- equal in the free symmetric monoidal category.
--
-- All `decode-rel`/`bridge`/`unflatten`-flavoured plumbing has been
-- factored out: the postulate conclusion is the plain `_‚ČąTerm_`
-- equality between two `HomTerm A B`s built from
-- `id, őĽ‚áí, őĽ‚áź, ŌĀ‚áí, ŌĀ‚áź, őĪ‚áí, őĪ‚áź, ŌÉ, _‚ąė_, _‚äó‚āĀ_`.  The constructive
-- discharge ultimately requires extending
-- `Categories.MonoidalCoherence.Solver` (currently Mac Lane only) to
-- handle ŌÉ via permutation tracking ‚ÄĒ see the header for the path.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Extract the underlying permutation of a structural HomTerm.
--
-- A 0-edge hypergraph IS a permutation (with labels) between its boundary
-- atom lists.  We extract this permutation by structural induction on
-- `Structural`, using only the propositional permutation combinators
-- (`refl`, `prep`, `swap`, `trans`) and standard list-permutation lemmas
-- (`++-comm`, `++-assoc`, `++-identity ≥`, `++‚Āļ`).
--
-- The directions:
--   * `id        : A ‚Üí A`              ‚Ü¶ refl
--   * `őĽ‚áí : I‚äóA ‚Üí A`,  `őĽ‚áź : A ‚Üí I‚äóA`  ‚Ü¶ refl     ([] ++ xs ‚Č° xs definitionally)
--   * `ŌĀ‚áí : A‚äóI ‚Üí A`                   ‚Ü¶ ++-identity ≥
--   * `ŌĀ‚áź : A ‚Üí A‚äóI`                   ‚Ü¶ sym (++-identity ≥)
--   * `őĪ‚áí : (A‚äóB)‚äóC ‚Üí A‚äó(B‚äóC)`         ‚Ü¶ ‚Ü≠-reflexive (++-assoc)
--   * `őĪ‚áź : A‚äó(B‚äóC) ‚Üí (A‚äóB)‚äóC`         ‚Ü¶ sym
--   * `ŌÉ  : A‚äóB ‚Üí B‚äóA`                 ‚Ü¶ ++-comm
--   * `_‚ąė_`                            ‚Ü¶ Perm.trans (note: h ‚ąė k goes k then h)
--   * `_‚äó‚āĀ_`                           ‚Ü¶ PermProp.++‚Āļ

Structural-to-perm
  : ‚ąÄ {A B} {f : HomTerm A B}
  ‚Üí Structural f ‚Üí flatten A ‚Ü≠ flatten B
Structural-to-perm (structural-id {A}) = Perm.refl
Structural-to-perm structural-őĽ‚áí        = Perm.refl
Structural-to-perm structural-őĽ‚áź        = Perm.refl
Structural-to-perm (structural-ŌĀ‚áí {A})  = PermProp.++-identity ≥ (flatten A)
Structural-to-perm (structural-ŌĀ‚áź {A})  = Perm.‚Ü≠-sym (PermProp.++-identity ≥ (flatten A))
Structural-to-perm (structural-őĪ‚áí {A} {B} {C}) =
  Perm.‚Ü≠-reflexive (Data.List.Properties.++-assoc (flatten A) (flatten B) (flatten C))
Structural-to-perm (structural-őĪ‚áź {A} {B} {C}) =
  Perm.‚Ü≠-sym (Perm.‚Ü≠-reflexive (Data.List.Properties.++-assoc (flatten A) (flatten B) (flatten C)))
Structural-to-perm (structural-ŌÉ {A} {B}) =
  PermProp.++-comm (flatten A) (flatten B)
Structural-to-perm (structural-‚ąė sh sk) =
  Perm.trans (Structural-to-perm sk) (Structural-to-perm sh)
Structural-to-perm (structural-‚äó sh sk) =
  PermProp.++‚Āļ (Structural-to-perm sh) (Structural-to-perm sk)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Narrowed postulates.
--
-- The original `Structural-coherence-‚ČąTerm` is split into two pieces:
--
--   * `perm-eq-from-iso` ‚ÄĒ the iso `‚ü™ f ‚üę ‚ČÖŠīī ‚ü™ g ‚üę` forces the underlying
--     permutations to agree, propositionally.  Sound because both
--     hypergraphs have 0 edges (structural), so the iso IS just the
--     boundary permutation comparison.  Stated as propositional equality
--     of `Structural-to-perm` outputs.
--
--   * `Structural-coherence-from-perm-eq` ‚ÄĒ Mac Lane's symmetric monoidal
--     coherence on the structural fragment: two structural HomTerms with
--     the same underlying permutation are `‚ČąTerm`-equal.  This is a
--     clearly-bounded finite problem (permutation equality is decidable
--     and the SMC coherence theorem applies).
--
-- The original `Structural-coherence-‚ČąTerm` is then derived as a
-- *definition* (no longer postulated).

postulate
  perm-eq-from-iso
    : ‚ąÄ {A B} {f g : HomTerm A B}
    ‚Üí (sf : Structural f) ‚Üí (sg : Structural g)
    ‚Üí ‚ü™ f ‚üę ‚ČÖŠīī ‚ü™ g ‚üę
    ‚Üí Structural-to-perm sf ‚Č° Structural-to-perm sg

  Structural-coherence-from-perm-eq
    : ‚ąÄ {A B} {f g : HomTerm A B}
    ‚Üí (sf : Structural f) ‚Üí (sg : Structural g)
    ‚Üí Structural-to-perm sf ‚Č° Structural-to-perm sg
    ‚Üí f ‚ČąTerm g

-- Derived: combine the two narrowed postulates.
Structural-coherence-‚ČąTerm
  : ‚ąÄ {A B} {f g : HomTerm A B}
  ‚Üí Structural f ‚Üí Structural g
  ‚Üí ‚ü™ f ‚üę ‚ČÖŠīī ‚ü™ g ‚üę
  ‚Üí f ‚ČąTerm g
Structural-coherence-‚ČąTerm sf sg iso =
  Structural-coherence-from-perm-eq sf sg (perm-eq-from-iso sf sg iso)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Derived: lift `Structural-coherence-‚ČąTerm` through `bridge` and
-- `decode-roundtrip-rel` to the original `decode-rel`-shaped lemma.
--
-- The derivation is purely categorical (no further postulates): the
-- `bridge`-wrapping is a congruence with respect to `_‚ČąTerm_`, and
-- `decode-rel f ‚ČąTerm bridge f` for every `f` by `decode-roundtrip-rel`.

private
  open import Categories.Category using (Category)
  module FM = Category FreeMonoidal
  open FM.HomReasoning

  -- `bridge` is a congruence for `_‚ČąTerm_`.  Inlined here so the
  -- discharge module doesn't depend on the `DecodeRoundtrip` private
  -- helper.
  bridge-resp-‚ČąTerm
    : ‚ąÄ {A B} {f g : HomTerm A B}
    ‚Üí f ‚ČąTerm g ‚Üí bridge f ‚ČąTerm bridge g
  bridge-resp-‚ČąTerm f‚Čąg = refl‚ü©‚ąė‚ü® f‚Čąg ‚ü©‚ąė‚ü®refl

Structural-coherence
  : ‚ąÄ {A B} {f g : HomTerm A B}
  ‚Üí Structural f ‚Üí Structural g
  ‚Üí ‚ü™ f ‚üę ‚ČÖŠīī ‚ü™ g ‚üę
  ‚Üí decode-rel f ‚ČąTerm decode-rel g
Structural-coherence {f = f} {g = g} sf sg iso = begin
  decode-rel f   ‚Čą‚ü® decode-roundtrip-rel f ‚ü©
  bridge f       ‚Čą‚ü® bridge-resp-‚ČąTerm (Structural-coherence-‚ČąTerm sf sg iso) ‚ü©
  bridge g       ‚Čą‚ü® decode-roundtrip-rel g ‚ü®
  decode-rel g   ‚ąé

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Discharge the original postulate.
--
-- `Atomic f` + `nE ‚ü™ f ‚üę ‚Č° 0` ‚áí `Structural f` (rules out `Agen`).
-- For the atomic shapes routed into the `‚Ä¶-0E` case from
-- `AtomicCompound.dispatch-structural`, the atomic-side edge count is
-- 0 by construction (see `nE-{id,őĽ‚áí,őĽ‚áź,ŌĀ‚áí,ŌĀ‚áź,őĪ‚áí,őĪ‚áź,ŌÉ}` there) ‚ÄĒ we
-- recover that here by case-splitting on the `Atomic` witness rather
-- than threading the edge-count proof through the API.

-- The originally-postulated lemma.  Note: the `Atomic f` hypothesis
-- combined with the dispatch from `AtomicCompound.dispatch-structural`
-- guarantees that `f` is *not* `Agen` (the Agen branch routes to
-- `decode-rel-resp-‚ČÖŠīī-Agen-compound-1E` instead).  We extract a
-- `Structural f` witness by case-analysis on `Atomic f`, where the
-- `Agen` branch is dismissed via the iso witness's edge-count
-- transport (a `Fin 1 ‚ÜĒ Fin 0` contradiction).

-- The discharge of `decode-rel-resp-‚ČÖŠīī-atomic-compound-0E`.  Note we
-- *drop* the redundant `Compound g` hypothesis: under
-- `nE ‚ü™ g ‚üę ‚Č° 0`, the `Compound g` argument carries no information
-- beyond the boundary types, since `Structural g` is recovered from
-- the edge-count witness alone (see `nE-0‚ÜíStructural`).  Dropping it
-- breaks an otherwise-circular import between `AtomicCompound.agda`
-- (which defines `Compound`) and this module.  The caller in
-- `AtomicCompound.agda` ignores the redundant argument when wiring up.

decode-rel-resp-‚ČÖŠīī-atomic-compound-0E
  : ‚ąÄ {A B} {f g : HomTerm A B}
  ‚Üí Atomic f
  ‚Üí nE ‚ü™ g ‚üę ‚Č° 0
  ‚Üí ‚ü™ f ‚üę ‚ČÖŠīī ‚ü™ g ‚üę
  ‚Üí decode-rel f ‚ČąTerm decode-rel g
decode-rel-resp-‚ČÖŠīī-atomic-compound-0E {f = f} {g = g} af g-nE‚Č°0 iso =
  Structural-coherence
    (atomic‚Üístructural af)
    (nE-0‚ÜíStructural g g-nE‚Č°0)
    iso
  where
    -- The `Agen` branch of `Atomic f` is incompatible with
    -- `‚ü™ f ‚üę ‚ČÖŠīī ‚ü™ g ‚üę` when `nE ‚ü™ g ‚üę ‚Č° 0`: the iso induces a
    -- bijection `Fin 1 ‚ÜĒ Fin 0`, which is absurd.  We discharge it by
    -- routing `Ōą : Fin (nE ‚ü™ Agen _ ‚üę) ‚Üí Fin (nE ‚ü™ g ‚üę)` and then
    -- transporting along `nE ‚ü™ g ‚üę ‚Č° 0`.
    open import Data.Fin using (Fin; zero)
    open import Relation.Binary.PropositionalEquality using (subst; sym)

    Fin-zero-empty : Fin 0 ‚Üí ‚ä•
    Fin-zero-empty ()

    -- In the `Agen` branch of `Atomic f`, the original `iso :
    -- ‚ü™ f ‚üę ‚ČÖŠīī ‚ü™ g ‚üę` becomes `‚ü™ Agen h ‚üę ‚ČÖŠīī ‚ü™ g ‚üę` (with
    -- `nE ‚ü™ Agen h ‚üę ‚Č° 1`), so `Ōą zero : Fin (nE ‚ü™ g ‚üę) = Fin 0`.
    atomic‚Üístructural : Atomic f ‚Üí Structural f
    atomic‚Üístructural (atomic-Agen h) =
      ‚ä•-elim (Fin-zero-empty (subst Fin g-nE‚Č°0 (_‚ČÖŠīī_.Ōą iso zero)))
    atomic‚Üístructural atomic-id        = structural-id
